## Admin ERP Rules

- **Follow coding conventions** defined in `.claude/rules/admin-coding.md`.

### When modifying or adding admin code

- **Before creating new components/pages**:
  - Check existing patterns in `erp-admin/src/pages/` for page structure
  - Check if components exist in `ui-components` library before creating new ones
  - Follow existing service pattern in `erp-admin/src/services/`

### Key differences from erp-frontend

- Uses **React Router v6** (NOT TanStack Router)
- **Standalone project** (NOT Nx monorepo) - flat `src/` structure
- Extends **AdminApiService** (NOT ApiService from @shared)
- **Admin auth context** separate from main frontend auth
- Connects to **admin API** on port 3001 (`/admin-api`), NOT main API on port 3000

### Design and implementation constraints

- **Always follow**:
  - React Hook Form + Zod for all forms
  - React Query for server state
  - Service layer pattern (extend `AdminApiService`, never call axios directly)
  - Tailwind CSS with `tw:` prefix for ALL classes
  - `ui-components` library for generic components
  - i18n translation keys for ALL user-facing text
  - `AdminAuthRoute` for route protection (public/protected)
  - CSRF token management via axios interceptors
- **Path aliases**: `@/*` -> `src/*`, `ui-components`, `@ui/*`
- **Never use**: `any` type, hardcoded strings, `||` for defaults (use `??`)
